{
  "texts": [
    "see Cackett et al. 2021) and galaxy-galaxy lensing (for the mass partition between baryons/dark matter and the IMF, e.g. see Shajib et al. 2024 and Vegetti et al. 2024).",
    "Microlensing constitutes an additional observational probe based on an \"orthogonal\" set of assumptions, e.g.",
    "it is not sensitive to the brightness profile of AGN emission in the same way as reverberation techniques, nor does it critically depend on the shape of the mass profile of the lens and the macroscopically observed brightness distribution of the lensed source (shape of the arcs, rings, etc).",
    "As such, it can be combined with more traditional methods, for example, to study the kinematics and morphology of the BLR (Garsden et al. 2011) and to break the degeneracy between the stellar IMF and the dark matter fraction (Oguri et al. 2014).",
    "Moreover, microlensing provides the additional advantage of probing objects that may be hard to study with standard methods."
  ]
}